DESCRIPTION:A Weekend of Art\, Technology\, and Critical Play\n\nHow do we live with our machines? How do we listen to data\, or make a sound-map of a street? What does resistance or re-imagination look like in a world saturated by code?\n\nThis weekend-long gathering brings together artists\, technologists\, and curious thinkers to explore the layered relationships between art and technology. Not as a celebration of innovation for its own sake — but as an invitation to pause and reflect: How does technology shape the ways we move\, make\, feel\, and relate? What forms of labour\, story\, or care are embedded in our digital environments?\n\nAcross workshops\, conversations\, and film\, we’ll explore how artistic practices can help us sense\, question\, and reimagine the technologies that surround us. Whether you're an artist\, coder\, student\, or simply curious — join us to listen\, learn\, and experiment together.\n\nSaturday &amp\; Sunday\, 21st June &amp\; 22nd June\n\n- IMMATERIAL: SPATIAL AFFAIRS\n\nSaturday\, 21st June\n\n\n- Sound is a Place Too\n\n- Living With Machines: A Critical Approach to Technology in Art\n\nSunday\, 22nd June\n\n- The Human in the Data\, the Data in the Human\n\n- Taak\n\n&nbsp\;\n\n&nbsp\;
DTEND:20250622T133000Z
