DESCRIPTION:Mapping space\, story\, and presence through sound &amp\; code\n\nWhat if space could be heard instead of seen?\nThis beginner-friendly workshop led by Nanditi (cofounder\, Ajaibghar) explores sound as a way of mapping our surroundings. Combining dérive\, deep listening\, and creative coding with Sonic Pi\, participants will translate their sensory impressions into ambient compositions — sonospheres — that hold memory\, presence\, and narrative.\nA slow\, reflective space for listening\, experimenting\, and working playfully with sound and code. No prior experience required.\n\nParticipants will need:\n– Laptop\n– Wired headphones or earphones\n– Paper &amp\; pen\n– Sonic Pi installed on computer\n– Dolby On app installed on phone
